Package Concepts

Class Concept

  • java.lang.Object
    • AbstractObjects.ItemWithId
      • Concepts.Concept
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    DataObject, java.io.Serializable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    IndividualConcept, SetConcept

    public abstract class Concept
extends ItemWithId
implements DataObject, java.io.Serializable
    This is an abstract superclass of IndividualConcept and SetConcept. It contains almost all necessary methods for manipulating the concepts.
    See Also:

      • add

        public boolean add​(Attribute attribute,
                   DataObject value,
                   Scope scope,
                   Context context,
                   java.lang.StringBuilder errors)
        adds an unconstrained attribute-value pair to the concept. If the attribute is symmetric then the symmetry partner is added. If there is an inverse attribute then the inverse is also added. Reflexivity and transitivity are not treated here.
        Parameters:
        attribute - the attribute to be added
        value - the value to be added (as DataObject)
        context - the context where the objects live in.
        scope - the scope of the value to be returned.
        Returns:
        true if there was no error.

      • stream

        public java.util.stream.Stream<DataObject> stream​(Attribute attribute,
                                                  Context context)
        computes a stream of the attribute values without considering any constraints. The stream is a concatenation of the following streams:
        1. the concept itself if the attribute is reflexive 2. the concept's LOCAL attribute values of all attributes down the attribute hierarchy
        3. the superconcepts ALL attribute values up the concept hierarchy.
        If all this yields nothing then the search goes up the concept hierarchy.
        to find the first non-null default values.
        Notice that the result maybe non-null even if the stream is empty.
        Parameters:
        attribute - the corresponding attribute.
        context - the context where the objects live in.
        Returns:
        a stream of DataObjects, or null if there are none.

        3. the superconcepts ALL attribute values up the concept hierarchy.
        If all this yields nothing then the search goes up the concept hierarchy.
        to find the first non-null default values.
        Notice that the result maybe non-null even if the stream is empty.
        Parameters:

        context - the context where the objects live in.
        otherConstraints - a map of attribute - dataObject constraints.
        Returns:

      • getFirst

        public DataObject getFirst​(Attribute attribute,
                           Context context)
        returns the first attribute value without considering constraints. The search proceeds as follows:
        1. If the attribute is reflexive then just 'this' is returned.
        2. the first LOCAL attribute value down the attribute hierarchy is searched.
        3. the first ALL attribute value up the concept hierarchy is searched.
        4. the first DEFAULT attribute value up the concept hierarchy is searched.
        Parameters:
        attribute - the attribute for which the value is to be returned.
        context - the context where the objects live in.
        Returns:
        the first attribute value.

      • find

        public <T> T find​(Attribute attribute,
                  Context context,
                  java.util.function.Function<DataObject,T> function)
        searches through the concept's attribute values without considering constraints until the first function application returns non-null. The method searches for the non-null function value in the following order:
        1. if the attribute is reflexive then the function is applied to 'this'.
        2. it goes down the attribute hierarchy and checks the LOCAL attribute values.
        3. it goes up the concept Hierarchy and checks the ALL attribute values.
        4. it goes up the concept hierarchy and checks the DEFAULT attribute values.
        Type Parameters:
        T - the result type of the function
        Parameters:
        attribute - the attribute whose values are to be checked.
        context - the context where the objects live in.
        function - a function to be applied to the attribute values.
        Returns:
        the first non-null function application.

        searches through the concept's attribute values satisfying the constraints until the first function application returns non-null. The method searches for the non-null function value in the following order:

        2. it goes down the attribute hierarchy and checks the LOCAL attribute values.
        3. it goes up the concept Hierarchy and checks the ALL attribute values.
        4. it goes up the concept hierarchy and checks the DEFAULT attribute values.
        Type Parameters:

        Parameters:
        attribute - the attribute whose values are to be checked.
        context - the context where the objects live in.
        otherConstraints - the filter for the attribute values
        function - a function to be applied to the attribute values.
        Returns:

      • repositionConcept

        public boolean repositionConcept​(Context context)
        repositions the concept if it is affected by one or more of the derived concepts. All derived concepts are taken into account to reposition the concept. It may happen that the concept becomes a sub-concept of one or several derived concepts. It may also happen that a concept which is a sub-concept of a derived concept, but where the corresponding filter no longer returns true, is moved away form the derived concept.
        Parameters:
        context - the context where the concept lives in.
        Returns:
        true if the concept has actually been repositioned.

      • parseConceptHierarchy

        public static boolean parseConceptHierarchy​(java.lang.String line,
                                            java.lang.String namespace,
                                            Context context,
                                            java.lang.StringBuilder errors,
                                            int lineNumber,
                                            DataBlock dataBlock)
        This method parses a single line with the information: superconcept subconcept1, subconcept2,... All concept must be either unknown, or SetConcepts. The new super/subconcept relation is inserted into the concept hierarchy. Nothing is changed if some of the concepts are Individuals.
        Parameters:
        line - the line to be parsed
        namespace - the namespace prefix
        context - the context for the concepts
        errors - for appending error messages.
        dataBlock - the origin of the data
        Returns:
        success or fail

                                 java.lang.String namespace,
